parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and surging can cause the vehicle to lunge forward or backward without warning, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle surges forward or backward when shifting gears
the transmission hesitates or lurches
the vehicle idles hard
loud noises are heard from the transmission
the RPMs jump up and down
the vehicle accelerates without warning
the doors open warning light comes on
and the passenger seat belt opens.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Throttle Body and Carbon Buildup Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The throttle body and carbon buildup issues can cause the vehicle to decelerate or lose power, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle decelerates or loses power
the transmission fault and check engine indicators illuminate
the accelerator pedal is depressed but the speedometer shows a lower speed
the throttle body is full of carbon and needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure and Input Shaft Bearing Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure and input shaft bearing failure can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The transmission fails
the input shaft bearing fails
the vehicle idles hard
loud noises are heard from the transmission
the transmission needs to be replaced
and the vehicle is left stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the loss of essential information, such as speed, coolant temperature, and gas capacity, which can lead to accidents or make it difficult to operate the vehicle safely.
symptoms: The instrument cluster goes dark or loses power
the speedometer
coolant temperature
and gas capacity gauges fail to function
the passenger airbag deactivates
the rear backup lights illuminate permanently
and the instrument panel lights fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the electronic throttle control can cause the vehicle to lurch forward unexpectedly, making it difficult to control the vehicle and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle surges or lurches forward
the brakes are difficult to engage
and the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heated seat can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, and in extreme cases, can lead to a fire hazard.
symptoms: The driver's side heated seat fails to function
the passenger side heated seat remains functional
and the heated seat can catch fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unwanted sudden acceleration can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when the vehicle is in a stopped or slow-moving condition.
symptoms: The vehicle lunges forward when in drive while stopped
easing forward
and braking in parking lots and streets
the vehicle accelerates to a high rate of speed without warning
the vehicle lurches forward before reaching the gas pedal after removing it from the brake
the engine revs when the brake pedal is released.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Throttle body failure can cause unwanted sudden acceleration, stalling, and loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle lunges forward when in drive while stopped
easing forward
and braking in parking lots and streets
the vehicle accelerates to a high rate of speed without warning
the engine revs when the brake pedal is released
the service vehicle soon warning light illuminates.
